@realmoney Oct 18, 2019 | 11:41 AM EDT DOUG KASS Netflix Now I have shorted Netflix ($NFLX). Over the years I have written quite a lot about the company and will have more next week. Basically I believe Netflix is a disaster waiting to happen.

For now, consider: Look at net interest expense in the last several quarters - there has been a quantum increase (and it's a dangerous trend). The market is valuing foreign subs as equal to U.S. subs. Is an Indian sub worth the same as one in Indiana? I doubt it.

NO free cash flow. Suffice to say, competition is increasing exponentially. Netflix used to own kids. No longer. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @andrewrsorkin @carlquintanilla @riskreversal @guyadami @terranovajoe

@realmoney opener coming up Are There Really More Positives Than Negatives? I intently watched the business media over the last 48 hours - all 3 networks. Respectfully I almost thought I was living in a parallel universe. Can Mr. Market melt up into year end, sure, why not?

But it is delusional in interpreting historically low rates and everything else as positive without recognizing that earnings are inflated by them as well as by phony non-GAAP adjustments, that corporate credit is overburdened, and that all financial assets are inflated.
Raise your hand if you give a crap about WeWork's woes? I thought so... very few hands. @tomkeene
